x4freetext: the CN Van de Graaff accelerator of the
Legnaro National Laboratories
Targets were made of MgO
evaporated on gold. The Mg was 95.75% enriched in
25Mg. The nominal target thickness was 70 mug/cm**2
while the gold backing was 1 mg/cm**2 thick. The
oxide prevents the magnesium from being further
oxidized and keeps the 18O background constant during
the experiment.
10 BC501 liquid scintillators from the RIPEN
array (see REL-REF), as already done in a previous
experiment using a similar setup. Each detector has
an active cell of 12.5cm in diameter and 12.5cm in
length.
Two collimated Silicon detectors (1mm diam.)
were placed inside the chamber at a distance of 7 cm
from the target and at 150. degr. with respect to the
beam direction. The silicon detectors have been used
for two purposes:
i) to count the backward scattered alpha-ions for
cross section normalization,
ii) to monitor the target integrity and the possible
presence of contaminants.
